    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 996.2 Carrera 4S, featuring the iconic widebody silhouette and a naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six engine. This power unit utilizes VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve, delivering seamless power through a G96 six-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is paramount; the IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal remains bone dry. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, supported by an all-wheel-drive system that ensures neutral handling characteristics under high lateral G-loads. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers finished in Guards Red, clamping down on ventilated, cross-drilled rotors with zero lip wear. Every bushing, link, and damper remains in peak operating condition, providing the tactile steering feedback these hydraulic racks are legendary for. This is a turn-key example for the discerning purist.",
